        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-10-31T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-10-31T11:00:00-05:00" n="317"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d317">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.4016/1804: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-10-31T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 31, 1938—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 31—2:48 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>583. Reference my 582, October 29, 3 p.m. It is learned from American press and
                    other sources that a sort of “armistice” has been reached between Germany and
                    Poland with regard to the banishment from Germany of Polish Jews whose passports
                    were allegedly invalidated by decree of the Polish Government. Negotiations for
                    a final settlement of the matter are to be begun in Warsaw tomorrow. <pb
                        facs="0403" n="395" xml:id="pg_395"/> It is stated that Polish Jews now in
                    German jails have been released and that those who were in the process of being
                    deported but had not yet crossed the border are being returned to their homes.
                    The Polish Government is said to have agreed to permit the Jews already sent to
                    Poland from Germany to remain for the time being.</p>
                <p>By mail to Warsaw and London for Rublee.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
